A
f \in A
m= \min\limits_{x \in [0,1]} f(x) >0
\epsilon>0 
\epsilon<\min(m,1-||f'||_{\infty},|f''(0)|-2)
g \in B(f,\epsilon)
|g(x)-f(x)| \leq ||f-g||_{\infty} < \epsilon
g(x)>f(x)-\epsilon \geq m-\epsilon>0
||f'-g'||_{\infty}< \epsilon
||g'||_{\infty}<||f'||_{\infty}+ \epsilon <1
|f''(0)|-|g''(0)| \leq |f''(0)-g''(0)| \leq ||f''-g''||_{\infty}<\epsilon
|g''(0)| >|f''(0)|-\epsilon >2
g \in A
